description.narrative: The development objective of the proposed project is to reduce transport costs for users of provincial roads along selected corridors of the Norte Grande provinces, through the improvement of the quality of those roads and the introduction of improved road asset management tools and methods.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article IV Section 4.01 | Description :At least one of the Participating Provinces has entered into aParticipation, Transfer and Maintenance Agreement with the Borrower | Due Date :02-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement :Scehdule 2 Section I.B.1 | Description :The Borrower shall: (i) carry out the Project in accordance with theOperations Manual and the Environmental and Social Management Framework (including EMPs, RPF, IPPF and the Chaco IPP) | Frequency:Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I.C.1 | Description :Prior to carrying out any Subproject, the Borrower (through UCPyPFE)shall enter into an agreement with the corresponding Participating Province | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I.E.6 | Description :The Borrower through UCPyPFE shall ensure that the Chaco IdentifiedSub-Project is carried out in accordance with the Chaco IPP | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section II.B.4 | Description :The Borrower through the Ministry of Finance shall prior to the startof each calendar year create and maintain a specific budget line during project implementation to track Project expenditures |Frequency :Yearly
